    "description": {
      "value": "\r\n<p class=\"source\"><b>Source</b> <a title=\"PZO1121\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1601253907/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=1601253907&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwd20pfs-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">PZO1121</a></p>\r\n<p>A pox burster is an alchemically preserved animal bladder or gourd that has been filled with toxic, rotting materials. You can throw a pox burster as a <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Throw-Splash-Weapon\">splash weapon</a>. Treat this attack as a ranged <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Touch-Attacks\">touch attack</a> with a range increment of 10 feet. A direct hit forces a target to immediately make a DC 13 <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Fortitude\">Fortitude</a> save or contract filth fever. Every space adjacent to the target square of the pox burster is covered in <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/afflictions/diseases\">disease</a>-causing filth. For the next minute, any creature that is injured while in one of these spaces must also make a DC 9 <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Fortitude\">Fortitude</a> save or contract filth fever.</p>\r\n",
